.TH "__splice_from_pipe" 9 "__splice_from_pipe" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__splice_from_pipe \- splice data from a pipe to given actor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" __splice_from_pipe
.BI "(struct pipe_inode_info *pipe "  ","
.BI "struct splice_desc *sd "  ","
.BI "splice_actor *actor "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pipe" 12
pipe to splice from
.IP "sd" 12
information to \fIactor\fP
.IP "actor" 12
handler that splices the data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function does little more than loop over the pipe and call
\fIactor\fP to do the actual moving of a single struct pipe_buffer to
the desired destination. See pipe_to_file, pipe_to_sendpage, or
pipe_to_user.
